This paper focuses on the problem of multi-label learning with missing labels, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The paper proposes a novel approach using mixed dependency graphs to handle missing labels and improve performance. This work is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and multimedia (cs.MM). However, given the focus on multi-label learning and image annotation/tag-based image retrieval, we believe that cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.MM.
